According to local media, the mental hospital has been ordered to issue a public apology and pay the man R10,000. JOHANNESBURG - A gay man in central China has reportedly won a lawsuit against a mental hospital over forced conversion therapy, in what activists say is the first such victory in the country.According to local media, the mental hospital has been ordered to issue a public apology and pay the man R10,000.The man had been forcibly admitted to the institution in 2015 by his wife and relatives and diagnosed with &quot;sexual preference disorder&quot;. He was forced to take medicine and receive injections before finally walking free after 19 days.